15/02/2011
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- An EU working group evaluating Bulgaria's efforts to join Schengen has approved two reports on the country related to the Schengen Information System and the state of the border with Turkey, Bulgaria's Ambassador to the EU, Boyko Kotsev, told journalists in Brussels on Monday (February 14th). 
He added that the experts approved the report on the Schengen system without comment, assessing that all membership criteria have been met. 
The report on the state of the border with Turkey was approved with some technical requirements still unmet. 
(BTA, Darik - 14/02/11)
